WEBVTT

00:00.610 --> 00:01.792
Hear the word of the Lord.

00:04.115 --> 00:07.760
After this, Joseph was told, behold, your father is ill.

00:09.002 --> 00:15.111
So he took with him his two sons, Manasseh and Ephraim, and he was told to Jacob, your son Joseph has come to you.

00:16.132 --> 00:26.066
Then Israel summoned his strength and sat up in bed, and Jacob said to Joseph, God Almighty appeared to me at loose in the land of Canaan and blessed me.

00:26.658 --> 00:36.111
and said to me, behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply you, and I will make you a company of peoples and will give you this land to your offspring after you for an everlasting possession.

00:37.172 --> 00:43.481
And now, your two sons who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt are mine.

00:44.662 --> 00:48.508
Ephraim and Manasseh shall be mine as Reuben and Simeon are.

00:49.389 --> 00:52.253
And the children that you fathered after them shall be yours.

00:52.954 --> 00:56.178
They shall be called by the name of their brothers and their inheritance.

00:56.866 --> 01:09.201
As for me, when I came from Padan to my sorrow, Rachel died in the land of Canaan on the way, when there was still some distance to go to Ephraath, and I buried her there on the way to Ephraath.

01:09.541 --> 01:10.723
That is Bethlehem.

01:12.044 --> 01:15.388
When Israel saw Joseph's sons, he said, who are these?

01:16.470 --> 01:20.494
Joseph said to his father, they are my sons whom God has given me here.

01:21.255 --> 01:23.618
And he said, bring them to me, please, that I may bless them.

01:24.559 --> 01:26.802
Now, the eyes of Israel were dim with age.

01:27.106 --> 01:28.107
so that he could not see.

01:28.969 --> 01:32.594
So Joseph brought them near him and he kissed them and embraced them.

01:33.034 --> 01:40.665
And Israel said to Joseph, I never expected to see your face and behold, God has let me see your offspring also.

01:40.705 --> 01:46.913
Then Joseph removed them from his knees and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.

01:47.454 --> 01:53.362
And Joseph took them both, Ephraim in his right hand towards Israel's left hand.

01:53.666 --> 01:58.851
and Manasseh in his left hand toward Israel's right hand and brought them near him.

01:59.813 --> 02:04.257
And Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on the head of Ephraim who was the younger.

02:04.978 --> 02:10.043
And his left hand on the head of Manasseh crossing his hands from Manasseh was the firstborn.

02:11.004 --> 02:15.769
And he blessed Joseph and said, The God before whom my father's Abraham and Isaac walked.

02:16.430 --> 02:20.114
The God who has been my shepherd all my life to this day.

02:20.578 --> 02:32.276
The angel who has redeemed me from all evil, blessed the boys, and in them let my name be carried on in the name of my father's Abraham and Isaac, and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.

02:33.698 --> 02:38.485
When Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him.

02:39.206 --> 02:47.459
And he took his father's hand to move it from Ephraim's head to Manasseh's head, and Joseph said to his father, not this way, my father, since this one is the firstborn.

02:47.499 --> 02:49.362
Put your right hand on his head.

02:49.858 --> 02:53.342
but his father refused and said, I know my son, I know.

02:54.904 --> 02:58.448
He shall also become a great people and he shall also be great.

02:59.089 --> 03:05.236
Nevertheless, his younger brother shall be greater than he and his offspring shall become a multitude of nations.

03:05.997 --> 03:13.185
So he blessed them that day saying, by you Israel will pronounce a blessing saying, God made you as Ephraim and as Manasseh.

03:15.088 --> 03:17.170
Thus he put Ephraim before Manasseh.

03:18.018 --> 03:25.872
Then Israel said to Joseph, Behold, I am about to die, but God will be with you and will bring you again to the land of your fathers.

03:25.972 --> 03:34.428
Moreover, I have given to you rather than to your brothers one mountain slope that I took from the hand of the Amorites with my sword and with my bow.

03:35.109 --> 03:40.980
Friends, the grass withers and the flowers fade, but the word of our God will stand forever.

03:41.440 --> 03:42.322
And you may be seated.

03:49.346 --> 03:50.287
Would you please pray with me?

03:55.252 --> 04:10.046
Blessed and merciful Father, creator of heaven and earth, as we turn now to the preaching of Your Word, we remember that we are people who are entirely dependent upon You.

04:12.969 --> 04:17.714
Lord, we need Your Spirit to come and to speak to us through Your Word.

04:19.074 --> 04:23.200
We need you to do what no preacher can do and what no hero can do.

04:24.202 --> 04:29.590
Would you please bring your word to life this morning that we would hear from you?

04:31.272 --> 04:36.500
All glory be to you, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, one God, now and forever.

04:37.702 --> 04:37.982
Amen.

04:40.907 --> 04:45.714
Friends, what is the mark that you want to leave on the world?

04:48.450 --> 04:53.757
I'm not just asking as Pastor Craig asked last week, what do you want people to say at your funeral?

04:53.817 --> 04:55.319
That might be the answer.

04:56.962 --> 05:05.333
But I mean, after you've been gone for 100 years, what mark do you hope to have made upon the world?

05:08.437 --> 05:14.966
Maybe it's your children and your children's children and your children's children's children and so on and so on.

05:16.708 --> 05:17.970
Maybe it's your job.

05:19.778 --> 05:22.781
We have a school, we employ educators at this school.

05:23.422 --> 05:27.106
So maybe your hope is that I'm gonna impact the next generation and they'll be formed.

05:27.646 --> 05:42.743
Maybe you have hopes and aspirations of running a business, forming some other institution, a hospital, that has a resounding impact that goes on and out way after you are gone.

05:44.685 --> 05:49.650
But what is the impact that you hope to make

05:49.858 --> 05:50.459
on the world.

05:52.081 --> 05:53.683
My guess is that you all have something.

05:55.084 --> 06:04.997
It's one of my really fun things about my job, working for a manual as I get to sit down with high school, usually juniors and seniors, and talk to them about the next steps of their life.

06:05.037 --> 06:07.760
What does that look like as they're going out into the world?

06:07.780 --> 06:08.962
What are they passionate about?

06:09.923 --> 06:12.206
What do they hope to be able to do?

06:12.246 --> 06:15.109
How do they want to make an impact on their life?

06:16.831 --> 06:18.994
And yet this looks different at every age.

06:20.930 --> 06:28.639
On average, the average American person in their career field changes their career eight times in the life of working.

06:30.782 --> 06:37.550
At each one of those breaks, if your identity is in your job in your career, you have to be wondering, what impact can I possibly make?

06:40.754 --> 06:45.640
As you step away from the career field, what impact am I making?

06:48.043 --> 06:50.546
The point is, friends, we want to have an impact

06:50.786 --> 06:51.948
that actually lasts.

06:53.229 --> 06:56.373
We want to leave a lasting mark on society.

06:57.895 --> 07:00.779
This is really what this text answers today.

07:00.859 --> 07:02.221
This is the question that it answers.

07:02.942 --> 07:05.665
What can we leave that lasts?

07:07.167 --> 07:10.912
What can we leave that lasts?

07:10.932 --> 07:13.455
And we'll see this answered in three movements.

07:14.977 --> 07:18.642
First, the covenant heritage versus one through seven.

07:19.042 --> 07:26.670
The covenant identity versus eight through 16, and covenant promises versus 17 through 22.

07:26.750 --> 07:29.153
What can we leave that lasts?

07:30.114 --> 07:33.558
Covenant heritage, covenant identity, and covenant promises.

07:35.480 --> 07:38.503
Just a quick note before we move into the text.

07:38.964 --> 07:48.594
As Pastor Craig mentioned last week, these next few chapters are actually pretty difficult to find good scholarly work on,

07:48.802 --> 07:51.326
to find people who have preached through them.

07:52.448 --> 08:02.062
In fact, most of the commentaries that I was looking at suggested, if you're going to handle Genesis 48, you might as well throw it together with 49 and 50, do it all in one thing, move on.

08:03.084 --> 08:09.494
So over the next couple of weeks, we're going to be slowing down and looking at passages that it's not the norm to do this with.

08:09.914 --> 08:12.338
They are kind of fly over texts.

08:12.514 --> 08:18.902
As we get to the end of Genesis, you're like 49 chapters in, you're so close to finishing, and you just cruise right on through.

08:18.942 --> 08:32.098
And I imagine this is often what happens sometimes with pastors, and they've been preaching through the book of Genesis, sometimes for years, and they have a chance to kind of condense things together a little bit, so they move pretty quickly.

08:33.219 --> 08:42.290
So our passage today, we're breaking it up into these three sections, because I really think there are these three sections that are helpful for us to understand and processing through.

08:42.754 --> 08:52.428
But really what we're going to do through these three sections is we're gonna look at what's happening through the eyes, try to relate and understand the three different character groups that we see.

08:53.008 --> 09:00.899
So in our first movement, we're gonna look at Jacob, try to understand Jacob's role in this first movement.

09:01.861 --> 09:07.248
So I invite you to look at your text here, chapter 48, verse one.

09:09.091 --> 09:11.314
After this, Joseph was told,

09:11.426 --> 09:21.215
Behold, your father is ill." So he took with him his two sons, Vanessa and Ephraim, and he was told to Jacob, your son Joseph has come to you.

09:22.417 --> 09:25.820
Then Israel summoned his strength and sat up in bed.

09:27.061 --> 09:31.265
You'll notice Moses here switches back and forth between Jacob and Israel.

09:33.087 --> 09:39.873
I don't think, and the vast majority of commentators agree, there's not any particular reason to what's going on there.

09:39.893 --> 09:40.754
We ought not.

09:40.866 --> 09:47.134
Look at when the different names are used and read them as though they are separate things or identifying different aspects of the same person.

09:47.595 --> 09:50.639
Rather, we just understand that this is the person who has two names.

09:51.080 --> 09:53.703
And so sometimes he's called one name and sometimes he's called the other name.

09:53.984 --> 09:57.048
And Moses freely interchanges between them in his writing here.

09:57.168 --> 10:02.315
So as we read, Jacob is dying and Israel sits up in bed.

10:02.716 --> 10:03.597
It's the same person.

10:04.278 --> 10:05.860
It's not two aspects of one man.

10:05.960 --> 10:07.082
It's the same person.

10:07.903 --> 10:10.386
But notice the setting that Moses gives for us here.

10:12.290 --> 10:13.992
Joseph hears that his father is dying.

10:15.353 --> 10:19.377
So Joseph grabs his two sons and books it.

10:20.198 --> 10:28.186
I mean, he gets there so quickly that the messenger that was just like told to go tell him doesn't make it back to let Jacob know that he's on his way.

10:28.827 --> 10:35.193
He beats the messenger so that someone has to say, your son got here and he's not even expected.

10:37.816 --> 10:39.858
So Jacob then,

10:41.090 --> 10:44.435
summoned his strength to sit up in bed.

10:45.677 --> 10:53.370
And this tells us everything that we need to know about the health status of the patriarch here.

10:53.390 --> 10:59.861
When it requires a summoning of strength to sit up in bed, the end is near.

11:02.064 --> 11:08.114
I don't know how many of you have ever been bedside with someone in their last hours or their last days.

11:09.634 --> 11:12.858
But if you've been there, then you understand what this is.

11:13.699 --> 11:17.504
The gathering of themselves to make meaningful eye contact.

11:18.865 --> 11:24.673
The pause for a second of a deep breath to squeeze a hand or to mouth, I love you.

11:27.056 --> 11:35.346
Jacob gathers his strength here because he still has work to do for his family.

11:37.986 --> 11:41.292
I want you to hear what he says as he gathers his strength up.

11:41.312 --> 11:42.555
We're here in verse three now.

11:43.977 --> 12:01.010
And Jacob said to Joseph, God Almighty appeared to me at loose in the land of Canaan and blessed me and said to me, Behold, I will make you fruitful and multiply you and I will make you a company of peoples and will give this land to your offspring after you for an everlasting possession.

12:03.170 --> 12:08.917
And now you're two sons who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you in Egypt are mine.

12:10.099 --> 12:13.783
Ephraim and Manasseh shall be mine as Reuben and Simeon are.

12:17.328 --> 12:23.696
Try to put yourself in Jacob's shoes for just a moment.

12:23.716 --> 12:25.739
I understand that we can't fully do that.

12:27.240 --> 12:31.666
But if you think of the last things that you get to say to someone,

12:32.386 --> 12:40.259
You summon your strength to sit up in bed, to communicate what we do in our culture is a goodbye, right?

12:41.180 --> 12:42.442
I mean, this is typically what people do.

12:42.482 --> 12:46.028
They reiterate on their deathbed, I want you to know how much I love you.

12:47.831 --> 12:52.518
Never forget that we love you, that we care about you.

12:54.141 --> 12:59.890
And this is a thing that we try to pass on, generation to generation.

13:01.986 --> 13:02.967
but not so with Jacob.

13:04.389 --> 13:06.272
It's not that Jacob doesn't love Joseph.

13:07.273 --> 13:09.577
Joseph knows that his father loves him.

13:11.700 --> 13:14.163
That's not what Jacob is wanting to pass on.

13:14.764 --> 13:19.951
That's not what he's giving to his son that lasts, but he's giving him is a covenant heritage.

13:22.395 --> 13:30.226
He says with his last few words, he continues on in the next chapter, but the last

13:30.562 --> 13:37.170
Several words that he's saying, he communicates, this is who our God is.

13:38.391 --> 13:50.746
The God of my father and my father's father, who's given us a promise, this is who our God is and your sons are now like my sons.

13:52.187 --> 13:53.128
I have adopted them.

13:55.832 --> 13:57.874
He says in verse six, he continues,

13:58.178 --> 14:00.742
And the children that you fathered after them shall be yours.

14:01.905 --> 14:07.715
They shall be called by the name of their brothers and their inheritance."

14:07.735 --> 14:09.217
This is weird to us.

14:10.640 --> 14:14.026
We have a hard time understanding what this means.

14:14.827 --> 14:17.772
We have a whole legal apparatus for adoption.

14:18.634 --> 14:23.282
If you have questions about it, I'm sure that Ryan would love to answer them after service.

14:23.842 --> 14:25.505
We have a whole way that this works.

14:25.525 --> 14:26.847
And here's how it doesn't work.

14:26.927 --> 14:30.554
It doesn't look like a grandfather on his deathbed saying, you know what?

14:30.594 --> 14:32.056
Your two kids are actually mine now.

14:33.859 --> 14:34.500
I can claim them.

14:35.122 --> 14:41.012
That's not the way that our society functions, but it's perfectly appropriate here.

14:42.635 --> 14:46.962
The patriarch looks at his son and says, those boys are mine.

14:48.482 --> 14:51.667
They're equivalent to my sons and other kids that you have in the future.

14:51.707 --> 14:53.791
Fine, they're yours, that's okay.

14:54.492 --> 14:55.454
But these boys are mine.

14:59.621 --> 15:02.886
Verse seven, ask for me when I came to Badan to my sorrow.

15:03.327 --> 15:05.190
Rachel died in a land of Canaan on the way.

15:06.813 --> 15:14.546
When there was still some distance to go to Ephraeth, and I buried her there on my way to Ephraeth, that is Bethlehem.

15:18.114 --> 15:25.882
And it is as though with those few words, God appearing to him, his wife dying.

15:26.963 --> 15:29.105
Jacob has rehearsed his entire life to his son.

15:32.128 --> 15:34.791
This is what he wants his son to carry on to remember.

15:36.092 --> 15:40.497
Remember who our God is and remember that I loved your mother.

15:43.480 --> 15:45.682
And that's what he gives to his son.

15:50.018 --> 15:54.323
Friends, what is it that you're hoping to pass down to the next generation?

15:58.308 --> 16:00.451
What do you want to give to your children?

16:01.912 --> 16:07.659
What do you want to give to the people that you get to interact with who are not your children?

16:08.961 --> 16:10.342
Perhaps you're single here this morning.

16:13.546 --> 16:14.147
So was Paul.

16:14.888 --> 16:16.690
He calls Timothy his son in the faith.

16:18.082 --> 16:22.026
So, assuredly, we don't get to sidestep that for lack of a spouse.

16:23.308 --> 16:25.691
Or maybe you are married and you don't have children.

16:29.455 --> 16:30.476
The question still stands.

16:31.077 --> 16:34.080
What do you hope to pass on to the next generation?

16:37.444 --> 16:42.730
It is my prayer, friends, that this is what we ultimately think about passing down to the next generation.

16:42.810 --> 16:44.212
Our covenant heritage.

16:44.732 --> 16:46.194
This is who our God is.

16:47.458 --> 16:49.081
This is what he has accomplished for us.

16:51.785 --> 16:55.951
It means so much more than the way that we typically think about inheritance.

16:57.213 --> 17:06.227
Land, material stuff, investments, a good work ethic.

17:10.234 --> 17:13.759
We have a covenant heritage that we can pass on to the next generation.

17:14.140 --> 17:15.602
And that is something that lasts.

17:16.450 --> 17:18.833
It's why we started a school.

17:21.155 --> 17:23.538
We want to pass on a covenant heritage.

17:25.860 --> 17:28.403
That's what Jacob shows us here in this text.

17:29.464 --> 17:31.607
Friends, is this not what God does for us?

17:33.269 --> 17:37.954
That he identifies us as his, that he gives us something we don't have any claim to?

17:37.994 --> 17:45.362
That he establishes who he has always been and who we will always be to remind us

17:45.954 --> 17:46.695
and comfort us.

17:49.498 --> 17:53.382
And so, this is what we ought to do as well.

17:53.422 --> 17:57.106
Not because Jacob did it, because this is how God acts.

17:57.627 --> 18:01.191
He gives us a covenant heritage.

18:01.211 --> 18:02.432
What can we leave that lasts?

18:02.492 --> 18:04.415
We can leave a covenant heritage.

18:04.575 --> 18:09.801
Now, second, a covenant identity, verses eight through 16.

18:11.362 --> 18:14.706
When Israel saw Joseph's sons, he said, who are these?

18:15.426 --> 18:19.251
Joseph said to his father, they are my sons whom God has given me here.

18:19.632 --> 18:21.895
And he said, bring them to me, please, that I may bless them.

18:23.276 --> 18:26.200
Now the eyes of Israel were dim with age so that he could not see.

18:26.961 --> 18:31.307
So Joseph brought them near him and he kissed them and embraced them.

18:32.709 --> 18:37.015
And Israel said to Joseph, I never expected to see your face.

18:38.036 --> 18:42.642
And behold, God has let me see your offspring also.

18:44.610 --> 18:47.314
Friends, this is an incredibly touching scene.

18:48.435 --> 18:53.983
I hope that you can feel the emotion of it in spite of some of its familiarity.

18:56.166 --> 19:00.032
A man who is blinded with age, you know, he's 147 years old.

19:03.277 --> 19:07.943
Says to his beloved son, Joseph, I never thought I would see you again.

19:08.684 --> 19:12.690
And now I'm beholding your children.

19:15.010 --> 19:22.398
What a tremendous blessing that this is to Jacob, that these boys are to him.

19:23.279 --> 19:25.702
What a kindness that God has given to him.

19:28.865 --> 19:36.613
So he claims these boys as though they were his own, because in a manner of speaking, he lost Joseph.

19:38.075 --> 19:40.818
To be sure, Joseph is still his son.

19:42.530 --> 19:45.374
But in what way does Joseph actually need Jacob?

19:46.576 --> 19:49.921
And what way does he need a father to provide for him in the way that a father would typically provide?

19:50.262 --> 19:52.465
And the answer is he doesn't.

19:53.407 --> 19:56.231
In fact, we see Joseph now providing for Jacob.

19:56.251 --> 19:59.536
We see this inversion that happened in this last chapter.

20:00.858 --> 20:11.154
And so he brings these sons to him and he rejoices in verse 11, and Israel said to Joseph, I never expected to see your face.

20:12.386 --> 20:16.170
Then Joseph removed them from his knees and he bowed himself with his face toward the earth.

20:16.590 --> 20:21.095
And Joseph took them both Ephraim in his right hand towards Israel's left hand.

20:21.676 --> 20:27.161
And Manasseh in his left hand towards Israel's right hand and brought them near him.

20:27.181 --> 20:37.792
And Israel stretched out his right hand and laid it on the head of Ephraim who was the younger and the left hand on the head of Manasseh, crossing his hands for Manasseh was the firstborn.

20:39.534 --> 20:39.634
Okay.

20:41.410 --> 20:42.773
It goes into great detail here.

20:42.853 --> 20:44.778
And I hope you can picture this in your mind.

20:46.001 --> 20:50.652
These sons are brought and Joseph and Jacob are facing each other, right?

20:50.832 --> 20:53.499
So one's left is the other one's right and one's right is the other one's left.

20:53.819 --> 20:59.954
And these boys are put in front of Jacob to bless by Joseph.

21:00.610 --> 21:03.855
And Joseph understands the cultural standards and what happens.

21:04.236 --> 21:09.685
He gets in a way that we don't understand that somehow the blessing of the right hand is more significant than the blessing of the left hand.

21:10.185 --> 21:11.407
And there's something going on there.

21:11.688 --> 21:17.878
And so he puts the boys where they're supposed to be in good and proper order, the oldest one on the right, the youngest one on the left.

21:19.761 --> 21:23.367
But then Jacob does what we wouldn't expect.

21:26.051 --> 21:27.954
Sorry about that beard hair and the mic.

21:30.050 --> 21:32.773
Jacob also understands the cultural expectations.

21:35.255 --> 21:36.877
But he understands something that Joseph doesn't.

21:38.038 --> 21:50.270
In some prophetic way that we don't have record of, Jacob knows that God is going to bless Ephraim, more than Manasseh.

21:50.290 --> 21:54.975
And so he reverses his hands and he gives this blessing to the boys.

21:55.636 --> 21:57.938
Verse 15, and he blessed Joseph and said,

21:58.370 --> 22:01.573
The God before whom my father's Abraham and Isaac walked.

22:02.354 --> 22:05.857
The God who has been my shepherd all my lifelong to this day.

22:06.718 --> 22:13.805
The angel who has redeemed me from all evil, blessed the boys, and in them let my name be carried on.

22:14.325 --> 22:20.591
And the name of my father's Abraham and Isaac, and let them grow into a multitude in the midst of the earth.

22:23.794 --> 22:27.858
These boys are not really boys.

22:30.114 --> 22:40.404
If you remember from last week, Pastor Craig was talking about the 17 years that had passed since Jacob had come into the land of Egypt.

22:41.705 --> 22:51.455
And we know that these boys were born sometime in this seven year period of prosperity, then there's these two years of famine and then Jacob shows up.

22:52.396 --> 22:56.120
So if we do the math, they're at least 19 years old.

22:57.101 --> 22:58.642
Perhaps as old as 26.

22:59.522 --> 23:09.315
somewhere in that range, which makes the reading of this even stranger, right?

23:09.335 --> 23:18.568
This blessing makes a ton of sense if we're talking about like a toddler or a baby or a small child, but these are not malleable children.

23:18.648 --> 23:29.202
These are men who have been raised in Pharaoh's household to be sure they are grandsons of Jacob, but they're also grandsons of

23:29.346 --> 23:31.088
priestess of a pagan god.

23:35.153 --> 23:41.901
These are Egyptian boys with Egyptian names raised in an Egyptian culture eating Egyptian food.

23:41.941 --> 23:44.004
They wore Egyptian clothes.

23:44.024 --> 23:45.966
They smelled like Egyptians.

23:46.006 --> 23:49.270
They were, for all intents and purposes, Egyptians.

23:51.113 --> 23:55.538
Now, to be sure, we know that Joseph has been practicing his faith so we can

23:55.842 --> 23:59.367
be certain that he is raising his sons in accordance with his faith.

24:01.269 --> 24:04.554
But the culture all around them was Egyptian.

24:07.198 --> 24:15.289
How bizarre, how strange that when Jacob is promising where his line will continue, he says, yeah, those two Egyptian boys.

24:16.851 --> 24:20.356
They're the ones that are gonna carry out my line.

24:20.376 --> 24:23.480
And of course, we know that that's not Jacob's words deciding that.

24:23.520 --> 24:24.882
He is prophesying.

24:26.146 --> 24:31.934
And so it makes it even stranger that God would say, you know how I'm going to fulfill my purpose?

24:33.576 --> 24:34.197
Yeah, that's right.

24:34.277 --> 24:39.504
Through those two, not the insiders, the outsiders.

24:42.028 --> 24:48.176
Friends, like I said, in the second point, you understand the role of the boys because this is us.

24:49.258 --> 24:49.799
You see this?

24:49.839 --> 24:50.359
This is us.

24:51.181 --> 24:55.186
We're those outside of the covenant community brought in to the covenant community.

24:55.458 --> 25:00.666
By the beloved Son brought to the Father that He would embrace us and adopt us and bless us.

25:02.849 --> 25:15.970
To be sure, not physically brought near, but in Christ's life, death, burial, resurrection, and ascension, we are brought to the Father and adopted into His family.

25:16.951 --> 25:19.616
We who are outside now been brought in.

25:21.158 --> 25:23.762
This is what God accomplishes for us.

25:23.970 --> 25:28.634
He gives us a new identity, a covenant identity.

25:29.195 --> 25:32.698
Identity that is based on him and what he has done and not ourselves.

25:36.021 --> 25:39.425
One quick aside, and it isn't aside, so I'm actually going to step aside.

25:40.466 --> 25:45.650
If you look ahead in verse 20, we already read it and talked about this, or read it at least.

25:45.991 --> 25:47.772
In verse 20, we will talk about this.

25:48.633 --> 25:50.315
You see that there's a blessing that's given.

25:50.335 --> 25:53.778
And this blessing is actually still given today by

25:53.922 --> 26:08.000
practicing Jews by devoted Jews, they give their son this blessing every Friday, this continual ongoing ritualistic rite that they have every Friday, they bless their sons, saying they would be as Manasseh and Ephraim.

26:10.122 --> 26:19.714
And the reason why they do that is because they pick up on a theme that starts in the very beginning of Genesis and actually comes to a head here.

26:20.956 --> 26:22.898
You see, Manasseh and Ephraim,

26:23.458 --> 26:27.563
are the first brothers that we ever see that don't compete with each other.

26:29.686 --> 26:43.343
So even though this blessing is reversed and we would seem that you would have a brother who feels jilted or a brother who feels prideful or anger, there'd be this fighting going on, we don't see any of that.

26:43.363 --> 26:52.434
Finally stopping this generational feud between brothers that was going on since Cain and Abel, we don't see that.

26:52.674 --> 27:01.666
I do think we're supposed to see ourselves in the text here in this movement as the brothers that are brought near to the father and adopted into his family by the beloved son.

27:02.047 --> 27:03.649
I think we're supposed to see ourselves here.

27:04.590 --> 27:13.543
I also think, perhaps, maybe that we should consider the unity and the accord that these brothers had with one another.

27:16.847 --> 27:21.874
Christ said that they will know that you are my followers, by your love,

27:22.146 --> 27:22.727
for one another.

27:24.208 --> 27:25.850
So friends, would that be what marks us?

27:26.851 --> 27:34.878
If there is any in the church or Christians outside of the church that you have conflict with, I would implore you.

27:36.260 --> 27:37.121
Try to make that right.

27:38.122 --> 27:39.263
Do not let that fester.

27:41.985 --> 27:50.994
Because of the identity that you have, because of the identity the other person has, because you belong to the same covenant, you can work towards peace.

27:51.746 --> 27:56.774
When that is secure, we can establish peace and forgiveness.

27:58.177 --> 28:00.040
What can we leave that lasts?

28:00.120 --> 28:06.190
We can leave a covenant heritage, a covenant identity, and now finally, verse 17, covenant promises.

28:08.614 --> 28:13.842
When Joseph saw that his father laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him.

28:14.804 --> 28:18.610
And he took his father's hand to move it from Ephraim's head to Manasseh's head.

28:20.226 --> 28:29.020
And Joseph said to his father, not this way, my father, since this one is the first one, put your right hand on his head.

28:32.125 --> 28:33.086
You guys see what's happening?

28:33.808 --> 28:34.469
You understand?

28:35.270 --> 28:47.890
As we think about Joseph here in this situation, again, I think we're supposed to see in this movement here and understand that we are often Joseph.

28:49.122 --> 28:50.785
actually not so well-equipped.

28:52.908 --> 28:55.051
Remember, Jacob is blind.

28:55.111 --> 28:57.735
He doesn't recognize the human beings that are brought in front of him.

28:57.755 --> 29:01.081
He actually can't see who's who.

29:01.101 --> 29:09.514
And so as he crosses his hands, Joseph might be thinking, oh, no, dad, dad, dad, dad, you don't understand.

29:10.615 --> 29:11.517
It's this one.

29:12.879 --> 29:13.720
This is the one.

29:15.163 --> 29:17.426
Maybe he thinks that his dad is senile,

29:17.730 --> 29:18.351
Who knows?

29:18.411 --> 29:19.292
But here's what we do know.

29:19.653 --> 29:21.475
Joseph has perfectly good working eyes.

29:23.418 --> 29:37.217
Joseph was the one who actually had the foresight for in the seven years of plenty to save up enough grain so that, I don't know, all of Egypt and really the known world around there could not starve to death and die.

29:38.919 --> 29:39.400
Pretty good.

29:41.763 --> 29:44.146
Think of what Joseph accomplished in the last chapter.

29:45.762 --> 29:53.233
All of the known wealth in the area, all of the material money people had to spend, they came to Egypt and they gave it to Joseph.

29:54.975 --> 29:59.702
And then all of the herds, they came to Egypt and they gave them to Joseph.

30:00.162 --> 30:06.651
And then in perpetuity, a 20% tax forever and ever on all of the land, they came and they gave it to Joseph.

30:06.691 --> 30:09.556
Now he's not collecting it for himself, he's collecting it for Pharaoh.

30:09.576 --> 30:14.162
But the point stands, there is no one else in this room who

30:14.498 --> 30:17.421
is so well equipped to be able to handle a situation.

30:17.481 --> 30:22.185
And yet he's wrong.

30:27.350 --> 30:29.973
The other option of what could be going on here, it's possible.

30:30.854 --> 30:34.938
Maybe Joseph is remembering his father's previous betrayals.

30:36.439 --> 30:43.346
His father's a trickster, a manipulator, a liar, someone who says the thing that's convenient rather than the thing that's true.

30:43.682 --> 30:45.264
who say whatever it takes to get his way.

30:45.905 --> 30:50.050
So maybe Joseph is seeing his father act and is saying, no, dad, no.

30:50.811 --> 30:54.756
In fact, in here when he says the father laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him.

30:55.176 --> 30:58.300
Some translations say it was evil in his sight.

31:01.424 --> 31:06.050
So maybe he's reacting to this thing where he thinks his father is again being manipulative.

31:09.214 --> 31:12.818
Or maybe he just thinks that his dad's wrong and he knows better.

31:16.546 --> 31:21.132
Joseph is actually being very reasonable, very reasonable.

31:21.152 --> 31:21.833
And we do this too.

31:23.556 --> 31:24.377
We question things.

31:24.417 --> 31:27.521
We wonder, again, I think very often we're not half this reasonable.

31:29.163 --> 31:39.057
But when God crosses his hands in the pouring out of blessings in our life, when it's not the way that we would have written it, not the way that we expect it, we question.

31:41.801 --> 31:42.802
And look at how

31:43.234 --> 31:45.597
God through Jacob answers Joseph.

31:45.637 --> 31:46.519
Look at the tenderness.

31:47.840 --> 31:52.226
But his father refused and said, I know my son, I know.

31:53.829 --> 31:56.913
He also shall become a people and he also shall be great.

31:57.033 --> 31:59.697
Nevertheless, his younger brother shall be greater than he.

32:00.278 --> 32:02.461
And his offspring shall become a multitude of nations.

32:02.881 --> 32:09.230
So he blessed them that day saying, by you, Israel will pronounce blessing saying, God make you as Ephraim and Manasseh.

32:10.432 --> 32:12.114
Thus he put Ephraim before Manasseh.

32:12.674 --> 32:18.464
Then Israel said to Joseph, behold, I am about to die, but God will be with you.

32:19.586 --> 32:21.369
And we'll bring you again to the land of your fathers.

32:21.449 --> 32:32.367
Moreover, I have given to you, rather than to your brothers, one mountain slope that I took from the hand of the Amorites with my sword and with my bow."

32:32.387 --> 32:33.970
He doesn't withhold a blessing.

32:37.896 --> 32:38.898
He comforts his son.

32:42.114 --> 32:45.900
He reminds his son of how great the blessing of both of his children will be.

32:45.940 --> 32:51.268
And then he boos beyond that and blesses his son.

32:51.328 --> 32:57.879
Reminds him of who his God and father is and said, and I'm giving you this particular slope.

32:59.842 --> 33:10.098
Before I start handing out stuff to your brothers, which is what happens in the next chapter, Joseph, I'm giving you this land right here, this slope that I won myself.

33:13.538 --> 33:31.218
I think often we can have an idea and a concern that we can't question things, that we can't ask questions, that we can't actually wrestle with things that are real and troublesome and problematic.

33:33.160 --> 33:41.650
Because if we do, God's gonna smite us, or that God can't hold up to our real questionings,

33:44.802 --> 33:53.476
And so we end up believing that what we have to do is believe things blindly or deconstruct our Christianity.

33:56.340 --> 34:00.266
Beloved of God, that is not the picture that the Bible paints.

34:03.712 --> 34:08.860
Friends, you, like Joseph, can ask the hard questions.

34:09.741 --> 34:12.946
Joseph tries to correct his father in the midst of him prophesying.

34:15.970 --> 34:29.809
It's okay to have questions, to wrestle with things, to bring them to God, that God could again encourage us of the promises that He has for us, because that is what lasts.

34:30.230 --> 34:35.797
It transcends the struggles that we have, the questions that we wrestle with on a day to day base of God.

34:35.837 --> 34:39.122
If you're real, why would you not stop this?

34:41.538 --> 34:46.926
The promises that God gives are true forever and ever in a way that that situation is not.

34:50.691 --> 34:57.361
And if you know saints who have suffered and lived long lives, then you know they will tell you again and again.

34:58.042 --> 34:59.605
They had no idea what God was doing.

35:00.266 --> 35:07.236
And they look back in retrospect and they see clearly and they can give thanks to God for things that they groaned over.

35:08.217 --> 35:11.442
Not all things, but certainly the majority.

35:14.594 --> 35:16.998
Friends, these are the things that last.

35:18.019 --> 35:20.063
What can we leave that lasts?

35:20.964 --> 35:25.672
We can leave a covenant heritage, a covenant identity, covenant promises.

35:26.934 --> 35:29.137
These are things that Christ has given to us.

35:30.559 --> 35:34.305
We've inherited a heritage that establishes our identity.

35:36.929 --> 35:38.852
We have access to God's promises.

35:40.215 --> 35:42.418
So because of this, friends, I pray that you

35:42.946 --> 35:58.645
would again dedicate yourself to the mark that you want to make on the world, that you would go out and do those things so that you can leave a covenant heritage, a covenant identity, and covenant promises.

35:59.866 --> 36:00.747
Would you please pray with me?

36:07.075 --> 36:12.882
God of all mercy and grace, Lord, we thank you for your word

36:13.634 --> 36:16.058
We thank you how you point us to Christ.

36:17.119 --> 36:42.418
We thank you for your gospel, that you bring us near to you who have no claim on you, that you give us a new identity, that you adopt us to sons and daughters, that you then empower us to go out, to bring others into your kingdom, to bring your kingdom about on earth as it is in heaven.

36:43.970 --> 36:45.316
We thank you for this privilege.

36:45.336 --> 36:47.305
We pray that you would strengthen us to this end.

36:48.330 --> 36:49.495
We ask this in Christ's name.

36:50.600 --> 36:50.962
Amen.

